◆ tinfl_status

enum tinfl_status
Enumerator
TINFL_STATUS_FAILED_CANNOT_MAKE_PROGRESS 
TINFL_STATUS_BAD_PARAM 
TINFL_STATUS_ADLER32_MISMATCH 
TINFL_STATUS_FAILED 
TINFL_STATUS_DONE 
TINFL_STATUS_NEEDS_MORE_INPUT 
TINFL_STATUS_HAS_MORE_OUTPUT 
814 {
815 /* This flags indicates the inflator needs 1 or more input bytes to make forward progress, but the caller is indicating that no more are available. The compressed data */
816 /* is probably corrupted. If you call the inflator again with more bytes it'll try to continue processing the input but this is a BAD sign (either the data is corrupted or you called it incorrectly). */
817 /* If you call it again with no input you'll just get TINFL_STATUS_FAILED_CANNOT_MAKE_PROGRESS again. */
818 TINFL_STATUS_FAILED_CANNOT_MAKE_PROGRESS = -4,
819
820 /* This flag indicates that one or more of the input parameters was obviously bogus. (You can try calling it again, but if you get this error the calling code is wrong.) */
821 TINFL_STATUS_BAD_PARAM = -3,
822
823 /* This flags indicate the inflator is finished but the adler32 check of the uncompressed data didn't match. If you call it again it'll return TINFL_STATUS_DONE. */
824 TINFL_STATUS_ADLER32_MISMATCH = -2,
825
826 /* This flags indicate the inflator has somehow failed (bad code, corrupted input, etc.). If you call it again without resetting via tinfl_init() it it'll just keep on returning the same status failure code. */
827 TINFL_STATUS_FAILED = -1,
828
829 /* Any status code less than TINFL_STATUS_DONE must indicate a failure. */
830
831 /* This flag indicates the inflator has returned every byte of uncompressed data that it can, has consumed every byte that it needed, has successfully reached the end of the deflate stream, and */
832 /* if zlib headers and adler32 checking enabled that it has successfully checked the uncompressed data's adler32. If you call it again you'll just get TINFL_STATUS_DONE over and over again. */
833 TINFL_STATUS_DONE = 0,
834
835 /* This flag indicates the inflator MUST have more input data (even 1 byte) before it can make any more forward progress, or you need to clear the TINFL_FLAG_HAS_MORE_INPUT */
836 /* flag on the next call if you don't have any more source data. If the source data was somehow corrupted it's also possible (but unlikely) for the inflator to keep on demanding input to */
837 /* proceed, so be sure to properly set the TINFL_FLAG_HAS_MORE_INPUT flag. */
838 TINFL_STATUS_NEEDS_MORE_INPUT = 1,
839
840 /* This flag indicates the inflator definitely has 1 or more bytes of uncompressed data available, but it cannot write this data into the output buffer. */
841 /* Note if the source compressed data was corrupted it's possible for the inflator to return a lot of uncompressed data to the caller. I've been assuming you know how much uncompressed data to expect */
842 /* (either exact or worst case) and will stop calling the inflator and fail after receiving too much. In pure streaming scenarios where you have no idea how many bytes to expect this may not be possible */
843 /* so I may need to add some code to address this. */
844 TINFL_STATUS_HAS_MORE_OUTPUT = 2
845} tinfl_status;

139 crc32 = (crc32 >> 8) ^ s_crc_table[(crc32 ^ pByte_buf[3]) & 0xFF];
140 pByte_buf += 4;
141 buf_len -= 4;
142 }
143

145 {
146 crc32 = (crc32 >> 8) ^ s_crc_table[(crc32 ^ pByte_buf[0]) & 0xFF];
147 ++pByte_buf;
148 --buf_len;
149 }
150
151 return ~crc32;
152}

7283 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pBuf);
7284 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_FILE_READ_FAILED);
7285 }
7286 cur_src_file_ofs += n;
7287
7288 if (pZip->m_pWrite(pZip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_dst_file_ofs, pBuf, n) != n)
7289 {
7290 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pBuf);
7291 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_FILE_WRITE_FAILED);
7292 }
7293 cur_dst_file_ofs += n;
7294
7295 src_archive_bytes_remaining -= n;
7296 }
7297
7298 /* Now deal with the optional data descriptor */
7299 bit_flags = MZ_READ_LE16(pLocal_header + MZ_ZIP_LDH_BIT_FLAG_OFS);
7300 if (bit_flags & 8)
7301 {
7302 /* Copy data descriptor */
7303 if ((pSource_zip->m_pState->m_zip64) || (found_zip64_ext_data_in_ldir))
7304 {
7305 /* src is zip64, dest must be zip64 */
7306
7307 /* name uint32_t's */
7308 /* id 1 (optional in zip64?) */
7309 /* crc 1 */
7310 /* comp_size 2 */
7311 /* uncomp_size 2 */
7312 if (pSource_zip->m_pRead(pSource_zip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_src_file_ofs, pBuf, (sizeof(mz_uint32) * 6)) != (sizeof(mz_uint32) * 6))
7313 {
7314 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pBuf);
7315 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_FILE_READ_FAILED);
7316 }
7317
7318 n = sizeof(mz_uint32) * ((MZ_READ_LE32(pBuf) == MZ_ZIP_DATA_DESCRIPTOR_ID) ? 6 : 5);
7319 }
7320 else
7321 {
7322 /* src is NOT zip64 */
7323 mz_bool has_id;
7324
7325 if (pSource_zip->m_pRead(pSource_zip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_src_file_ofs, pBuf, sizeof(mz_uint32) * 4) != sizeof(mz_uint32) * 4)
7326 {
7327 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pBuf);
7328 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_FILE_READ_FAILED);
7329 }
7330
7331 has_id = (MZ_READ_LE32(pBuf) == MZ_ZIP_DATA_DESCRIPTOR_ID);
7332
7333 if (pZip->m_pState->m_zip64)
7334 {
7335 /* dest is zip64, so upgrade the data descriptor */
7336 const mz_uint32 *pSrc_descriptor = (const mz_uint32 *)((const mz_uint8 *)pBuf + (has_id ? sizeof(mz_uint32) : 0));
7337 const mz_uint32 src_crc32 = pSrc_descriptor[0];
7338 const mz_uint64 src_comp_size = pSrc_descriptor[1];
7339 const mz_uint64 src_uncomp_size = pSrc_descriptor[2];
7340
7341 mz_write_le32((mz_uint8 *)pBuf, MZ_ZIP_DATA_DESCRIPTOR_ID);
7342 mz_write_le32((mz_uint8 *)pBuf + sizeof(mz_uint32) * 1, src_crc32);
7343 mz_write_le64((mz_uint8 *)pBuf + sizeof(mz_uint32) * 2, src_comp_size);
7344 mz_write_le64((mz_uint8 *)pBuf + sizeof(mz_uint32) * 4, src_uncomp_size);
7345
7346 n = sizeof(mz_uint32) * 6;
7347 }
7348 else
7349 {
7350 /* dest is NOT zip64, just copy it as-is */
7351 n = sizeof(mz_uint32) * (has_id ? 4 : 3);
7352 }
7353 }
7354
7355 if (pZip->m_pWrite(pZip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_dst_file_ofs, pBuf, n) != n)
7356 {
7357 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pBuf);
7358 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_FILE_WRITE_FAILED);
7359 }
7360
7361 cur_src_file_ofs += n;
7362 cur_dst_file_ofs += n;
7363 }
7364 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pBuf);
7365
7366 /* Finally, add the new central dir header */
7367 orig_central_dir_size = pState->m_central_dir.m_size;
7368
7369 memcpy(new_central_header, pSrc_central_header, MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE);
7370
7371 if (pState->m_zip64)
7372 {
7373 /* This is the painful part: We need to write a new central dir header + ext block with updated zip64 fields, and ensure the old fields (if any) are not included. */
7374 const mz_uint8 *pSrc_ext = pSrc_central_header + MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE + src_filename_len;
7375 mz_zip_array new_ext_block;
7376
7377 mz_zip_array_init(&new_ext_block, sizeof(mz_uint8));
7378
7379 MZ_WRITE_LE32(new_central_header + MZ_ZIP_CDH_COMPRESSED_SIZE_OFS, MZ_UINT32_MAX);
7380 MZ_WRITE_LE32(new_central_header + MZ_ZIP_CDH_DECOMPRESSED_SIZE_OFS, MZ_UINT32_MAX);
7381 MZ_WRITE_LE32(new_central_header + MZ_ZIP_CDH_LOCAL_HEADER_OFS, MZ_UINT32_MAX);
7382
7383 if (!mz_zip_writer_update_zip64_extension_block(&new_ext_block, pZip, pSrc_ext, src_ext_len, &src_file_stat.m_comp_size, &src_file_stat.m_uncomp_size, &local_dir_header_ofs, NULL))
7384 {
7385 mz_zip_array_clear(pZip, &new_ext_block);
7386 return MZ_FALSE;
7387 }
7388
7389 MZ_WRITE_LE16(new_central_header + MZ_ZIP_CDH_EXTRA_LEN_OFS, new_ext_block.m_size);
7390
7391 if (!mz_zip_array_push_back(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir, new_central_header, MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE))
7392 {
7393 mz_zip_array_clear(pZip, &new_ext_block);
7394 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_ALLOC_FAILED);
7395 }
7396
7397 if (!mz_zip_array_push_back(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir, pSrc_central_header + MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE, src_filename_len))
7398 {
7399 mz_zip_array_clear(pZip, &new_ext_block);
7400 mz_zip_array_resize(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir, orig_central_dir_size, MZ_FALSE);
7401 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_ALLOC_FAILED);
7402 }
7403
7404 if (!mz_zip_array_push_back(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir, new_ext_block.m_p, new_ext_block.m_size))
7405 {
7406 mz_zip_array_clear(pZip, &new_ext_block);
7407 mz_zip_array_resize(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir, orig_central_dir_size, MZ_FALSE);
7408 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_ALLOC_FAILED);
7409 }
7410
7411 if (!mz_zip_array_push_back(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir, pSrc_central_header + MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE + src_filename_len + src_ext_len, src_comment_len))
7412 {
7413 mz_zip_array_clear(pZip, &new_ext_block);
7414 mz_zip_array_resize(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir, orig_central_dir_size, MZ_FALSE);
7415 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_ALLOC_FAILED);
7416 }
7417
7418 mz_zip_array_clear(pZip, &new_ext_block);
7419 }
7420 else
7421 {
7422 /* sanity checks */
7423 if (cur_dst_file_ofs > MZ_UINT32_MAX)
7424 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_ARCHIVE_TOO_LARGE);
7425
7426 if (local_dir_header_ofs >= MZ_UINT32_MAX)
7427 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_ARCHIVE_TOO_LARGE);
7428
7429 MZ_WRITE_LE32(new_central_header + MZ_ZIP_CDH_LOCAL_HEADER_OFS, local_dir_header_ofs);
7430
7431 if (!mz_zip_array_push_back(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir, new_central_header, MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE))
7432 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_ALLOC_FAILED);
7433
7434 if (!mz_zip_array_push_back(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir, pSrc_central_header + MZ_ZIP_CENTRAL_DIR_HEADER_SIZE, src_central_dir_following_data_size))
7435 {
7436 mz_zip_array_resize(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir, orig_central_dir_size, MZ_FALSE);
7437 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_ALLOC_FAILED);
7438 }
7439 }
7440
7441 /* This shouldn't trigger unless we screwed up during the initial sanity checks */
7442 if (pState->m_central_dir.m_size >= MZ_UINT32_MAX)
7443 {
7444 /* TODO: Support central dirs >= 32-bits in size */
7445 mz_zip_array_resize(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir, orig_central_dir_size, MZ_FALSE);
7446 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_UNSUPPORTED_CDIR_SIZE);
7447 }
7448
7449 n = (mz_uint32)orig_central_dir_size;
7450 if (!mz_zip_array_push_back(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir_offsets, &n, 1))
7451 {
7452 mz_zip_array_resize(pZip, &pState->m_central_dir, orig_central_dir_size, MZ_FALSE);
7453 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_ALLOC_FAILED);
7454 }
7455
7456 pZip->m_total_files++;
7457 pZip->m_archive_size = cur_dst_file_ofs;
7458
7459 return MZ_TRUE;
7460}

6534 void *pRead_buf = pZip->m_pAlloc(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, 1, MZ_ZIP_MAX_IO_BUF_SIZE);
6535 if (!pRead_buf)
6536 {
6537 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_ALLOC_FAILED);
6538 }

6543 {
6544 size_t n = read_callback(callback_opaque, file_ofs, pRead_buf, MZ_ZIP_MAX_IO_BUF_SIZE);
6545 if (n == 0)
6546 break;
6547
6548 if ((n > MZ_ZIP_MAX_IO_BUF_SIZE) || (file_ofs + n > max_size))
6549 {
6550 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pRead_buf);
6551 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_FILE_READ_FAILED);
6552 }
6553 if (pZip->m_pWrite(pZip->m_pIO_opaque, cur_archive_file_ofs, pRead_buf, n) != n)
6554 {
6555 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pRead_buf);
6556 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_FILE_WRITE_FAILED);
6557 }
6558 file_ofs += n;
6559 uncomp_crc32 = (mz_uint32)mz_crc32(uncomp_crc32, (const mz_uint8 *)pRead_buf, n);
6560 cur_archive_file_ofs += n;
6561 }
6562 uncomp_size = file_ofs;
6563 comp_size = uncomp_size;
6564 }
6565 else
6566 {
6567 mz_bool result = MZ_FALSE;
6568 mz_zip_writer_add_state state;
6569 tdefl_compressor *pComp = (tdefl_compressor *)pZip->m_pAlloc(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, 1, sizeof(tdefl_compressor));
6570 if (!pComp)
6571 {
6572 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pRead_buf);
6573 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_ALLOC_FAILED);
6574 }
6575

6577 state.m_cur_archive_file_ofs = cur_archive_file_ofs;
6578 state.m_comp_size = 0;
6579

6581 {
6582 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pComp);
6583 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pRead_buf);
6584 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_INTERNAL_ERROR);
6585 }
6586

6588 {
6589 tdefl_status status;
6590 tdefl_flush flush = TDEFL_NO_FLUSH;
6591
6592 size_t n = read_callback(callback_opaque, file_ofs, pRead_buf, MZ_ZIP_MAX_IO_BUF_SIZE);
6593 if ((n > MZ_ZIP_MAX_IO_BUF_SIZE) || (file_ofs + n > max_size))
6594 {
6595 mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_FILE_READ_FAILED);
6596 break;
6597 }
6598
6599 file_ofs += n;
6600 uncomp_crc32 = (mz_uint32)mz_crc32(uncomp_crc32, (const mz_uint8 *)pRead_buf, n);
6601
6602 if (pZip->m_pNeeds_keepalive != NULL && pZip->m_pNeeds_keepalive(pZip->m_pIO_opaque))
6603 flush = TDEFL_FULL_FLUSH;
6604
6605 if (n == 0)
6606 flush = TDEFL_FINISH;
6607
6608 status = tdefl_compress_buffer(pComp, pRead_buf, n, flush);
6609 if (status == TDEFL_STATUS_DONE)
6610 {
6611 result = MZ_TRUE;
6612 break;
6613 }
6614 else if (status != TDEFL_STATUS_OKAY)
6615 {
6616 mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_COMPRESSION_FAILED);
6617 break;
6618 }
6619 }
6620
6621 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pComp);
6622
6623 if (!result)
6624 {
6625 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pRead_buf);
6626 return MZ_FALSE;
6627 }
6628
6629 uncomp_size = file_ofs;
6630 comp_size = state.m_comp_size;
6631 cur_archive_file_ofs = state.m_cur_archive_file_ofs;
6632 }
6633
6634 pZip->m_pFree(pZip->m_pAlloc_opaque, pRead_buf);
6635 }
6636
6637 {
6638 mz_uint8 local_dir_footer[MZ_ZIP_DATA_DESCRIPTER_SIZE64];
6639 mz_uint32 local_dir_footer_size = MZ_ZIP_DATA_DESCRIPTER_SIZE32;

6642 MZ_WRITE_LE32(local_dir_footer + 4, uncomp_crc32);
6643 if (pExtra_data == NULL)
6644 {
6645 if (comp_size > MZ_UINT32_MAX)
6646 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_ARCHIVE_TOO_LARGE);
6647

6649 MZ_WRITE_LE32(local_dir_footer + 12, uncomp_size);

6652 {

6654 MZ_WRITE_LE64(local_dir_footer + 16, uncomp_size);
6655 local_dir_footer_size = MZ_ZIP_DATA_DESCRIPTER_SIZE64;
6656 }

6659 return MZ_FALSE;
6660
6661 cur_archive_file_ofs += local_dir_footer_size;
6662 }

6665 {

6676 pZip->m_archive_size = cur_archive_file_ofs;

5815
5816 if (flags & MZ_ZIP_FLAG_WRITE_ZIP64)
5817 {
5818 /* We don't support converting a non-zip64 file to zip64 - this seems like more trouble than it's worth. (What about the existing 32-bit data descriptors that could follow the compressed data?) */
5819 if (!pZip->m_pState->m_zip64)
5820 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_INVALID_PARAMETER);
5821 }
5822
5823 /* No sense in trying to write to an archive that's already at the support max size */
5824 if (pZip->m_pState->m_zip64)
5825 {
5826 if (pZip->m_total_files == MZ_UINT32_MAX)
5827 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_TOO_MANY_FILES);
5828 }
5829 else

5836 }
5837

5839

5841 {
5842#ifdef MINIZ_NO_STDIO
5843 (void)pFilename;
5844 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_INVALID_PARAMETER);
5845#else
5846 if (pZip->m_pIO_opaque != pZip)
5847 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_INVALID_PARAMETER);
5848
5849 if (pZip->m_zip_type == MZ_ZIP_TYPE_FILE)
5850 {
5851 if (!pFilename)
5852 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_INVALID_PARAMETER);
5853

5855 if (NULL == (pState->m_pFile = MZ_FREOPEN(pFilename, "r+b", pState->m_pFile)))

5859 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_FILE_OPEN_FAILED);

5861 }

5879 return mz_zip_set_error(pZip, MZ_ZIP_INVALID_PARAMETER);

5881 /* Start writing new files at the archive's current central directory location. */
